WEBVTT

00:00.674 --> 00:01.635
Good morning, everybody.

00:03.438 --> 00:04.059
Glad you're here.

00:05.301 --> 00:06.423
Wanna start with the question?

00:07.504 --> 00:12.672
Have you ever tried really, really, really hard to fix something only to make it worse?

00:13.714 --> 00:14.294
Anybody else?

00:14.935 --> 00:15.276
Anybody?

00:15.576 --> 00:15.917
Anybody?

00:16.037 --> 00:16.177
Yeah.

00:17.559 --> 00:20.824
All you raising your hand, thank you for being honest.

00:21.485 --> 00:22.066
I'm just kidding.

00:23.138 --> 00:38.377
I remember very, it's kind of funny, the things I remember sometimes the most innocuous moments in life, like they shouldn't matter or stay in your memory, but there's a particular point I remember where I tried really hard to fix something and it didn't go well.

00:39.458 --> 00:52.754
I was a kid and I was trying to rewind the garden hose that had been time to water the plants and the hose was on one of those

00:53.186 --> 00:57.611
You know, things you can just crank and spin and you can just pull it and let it out.

00:57.671 --> 01:00.394
And so it was wrapped around the house or whatever.

01:00.454 --> 01:04.919
And I was sitting here just twisting it back up.

01:06.681 --> 01:18.674
Unfortunately, I was watching the hose like from the distance and not paying attention to the fact that it had got caught in the spoke.

01:21.218 --> 01:27.026
So I keep trying to turn it to wheel it back in and it stops.

01:29.209 --> 01:30.170
I can't get it to move.

01:32.213 --> 01:32.954
So what did I do?

01:34.617 --> 01:37.120
Well, I thought to myself, I guess I just got to push harder.

01:38.782 --> 01:42.267
And so I just kept with all of my might pushing.

01:42.748 --> 01:45.812
It kind of started to go, but it still kept getting stuck.

01:46.714 --> 01:49.938
I'm still oblivious to the fact that it's caught.

01:51.650 --> 01:54.894
And so I just push as hard as I can and then snap.

01:56.896 --> 01:58.137
The handle breaks right off.

02:00.380 --> 02:10.772
Now I just stood there outside stunned, wondering how I was going to explain why our hose reel no longer had a handle on it.

02:15.837 --> 02:20.082
I learned a couple important lessons that day, but there was one that stuck with me.

02:21.378 --> 02:23.881
Sometimes the problem isn't a lack of effort.

02:27.204 --> 02:30.388
Sometimes the problem is the kind of effort we're using.

02:33.491 --> 02:36.755
Because pushing harder doesn't fix everything.

02:38.937 --> 02:43.342
In fact, sometimes pushing harder is exactly what breaks it.

02:46.606 --> 02:50.450
And if we're honest, that's how a lot of us approach

02:51.042 --> 02:56.207
the Christian faith, the Christian life.

02:56.227 --> 03:15.305
We feel stuck, we see something in us that needs to change, we notice impatience maybe, frustration, pride building up, comparison with others, grumbling, and our instinct is the same as mine was with the hose.

03:16.887 --> 03:20.370
We try harder, we push more,

03:22.338 --> 03:24.021
We crank down on behavior.

03:25.363 --> 03:27.947
We white knuckle our obedience.

03:30.531 --> 03:35.638
But what if the Christian life isn't primarily about pushing harder?

03:37.722 --> 03:40.606
What if transformation doesn't start with more force?

03:43.230 --> 03:51.122
What if something deeper is happening inside that is more powerful, more capable,

03:52.546 --> 03:54.829
of bringing about the change that we know that we need.

03:58.473 --> 04:02.778
We are in the middle of studying through Philippians chapter two.

04:02.818 --> 04:09.045
TJ did an awesome, fantastic job in the first part last week.

04:09.986 --> 04:12.269
He actually preached through one of my favorite passages.

04:12.289 --> 04:20.338
I love the hymn about Jesus, about his humility, about his obedience to the Father,

04:21.602 --> 04:39.366
And obviously, those of us that are Christians believe that Jesus' faithfulness to the Father is what makes us in right relationship with the Father, what gives us salvation, what gives us a path toward righteousness.

04:42.851 --> 04:51.442
And so Paul's gonna carry on based on the humility and faithfulness of Jesus,

04:51.938 --> 04:54.542
letter to the Philippian Christians.

04:56.544 --> 05:11.525
And what we're gonna find when we look at verses 12 through 18 today, that the problem facing the Philippian Christians is not laziness, it's not lack of effort, but a misunderstanding about how real change happens.

05:13.788 --> 05:20.658
I tend to find that from a theological standpoint that this issue that Paul talks about in this section

05:21.602 --> 05:31.933
is one of the ones that becomes most misunderstood and creates much more weight on our shoulders as believers than we like to give credit for.

05:33.535 --> 05:49.592
And so if you have your Bibles or if you wanna follow on the screen, we're gonna look to Philippians chapter two verses 12 through 18 today and see what Paul says about this issue of pushing too hard and not realizing where real change comes from.

05:49.632 --> 05:51.314
Here's what he writes.

05:52.162 --> 06:07.105
says, therefore, my dear friends, just as you have always obeyed, so now, not only in my presence, but even more in my absence, work out your own salvation with fear and trembling.

06:08.407 --> 06:16.579
For it is God who is working in you, both to will and to work according to his good purpose.

06:17.821 --> 06:20.946
Do everything without grumbling and arguing.

06:21.314 --> 06:34.931
so that you may be blameless and pure, children of God who are faultless and a crooked and perverted generation among whom you shine like stars in the world by holding firm to the word of life.

06:35.712 --> 06:40.838
Then I can boast in the day of Christ that I didn't run or labor for nothing.

06:42.039 --> 06:50.930
But even if I am poured out as a drink offering on the sacrificial service of your faith, I am glad and I rejoice with all of you.

06:51.202 --> 06:56.968
In the same way, you should also be glad and rejoice with me.

06:59.731 --> 07:06.859
So in verse 12 here, Paul encourages all the Philippian believers to continue in their obedience to God.

07:08.441 --> 07:13.587
This was a church that was bound to Paul and his own predicament of being in chains.

07:14.007 --> 07:16.530
Remember, he writes this letter from prison.

07:17.474 --> 07:27.926
And of course, they have experienced being up against the world around them and living out their own faith, but they continued and have a reputation for being obedient in faith.

07:28.707 --> 07:39.941
And yet, when you are up against persecution, when you're up against trial, when you're up against difficulties in life, it is a day at a time sort of step of obedience.

07:40.782 --> 07:44.466
And so Paul still wants the right to encourage the Philippians

07:44.770 --> 07:47.653
to continue to be obedient as they already had been.

07:47.693 --> 07:53.099
And it is a continuance because they're already reputed as having been obedient before.

07:53.860 --> 07:55.942
So Paul is encouraging them to keep it up.

07:58.004 --> 08:00.006
But I want you to notice what he's also saying.

08:00.046 --> 08:04.491
He's saying, don't let your obedience depend on supervision.

08:05.372 --> 08:11.538
He encourages the Philippian disciples to keep obeying when no one's watching, including Paul himself.

08:11.842 --> 08:14.727
who's obviously absent because he can't physically be there.

08:15.208 --> 08:16.150
He's stuck in prison.

08:17.312 --> 08:22.320
But the second half of the verse has often troubled theologians and everyday Christians alike.

08:22.841 --> 08:28.131
Paul says to work out your own salvation with fear and trembling.

08:29.032 --> 08:31.737
Work out your own salvation with fear and trembling.

08:32.879 --> 08:36.946
But catch this, Paul does not say to work for your salvation.

08:39.106 --> 08:43.611
He says to work out your own salvation, not to work for your salvation.

08:43.671 --> 08:52.682
And so to put more succinctly, you've received salvation, now let it show up and show out in your daily life.

08:53.683 --> 08:54.504
That's what Paul says.

08:56.386 --> 09:00.411
Let what God has done inside of you be visible on the outside.

09:00.471 --> 09:06.738
Let Christ humility, as he described in Philippians 2, 6 through 11,

09:06.914 --> 09:10.077
become the culture that forms your words and deeds.

09:11.198 --> 09:17.004
Salvation isn't meant to sit inside us, it's meant to take shape in how we treat one another.

09:18.205 --> 09:25.072
And when Paul says fear and trembling, he's talking about our obedience being rooted in our reverence toward God.

09:28.135 --> 09:35.762
The book of Proverbs famously says that wisdom begins with fear of the Lord.

09:37.282 --> 09:37.582
fear.

09:38.884 --> 09:52.941
Now this isn't to mean being spooked out and go hiding, but to recognize his grander in our place and his good creation and to act accordingly with reverence.

09:54.523 --> 09:59.569
So it means living with awareness that God is holy, present, and at work.

09:59.589 --> 10:04.114
It means refusing to treat discipleship obedience to Jesus casually

10:04.514 --> 10:07.298
because the living God is shaping your life right now.

10:09.040 --> 10:25.481
But then in verse 13, and this is really vital what he does here, Paul immediately guards against self-powered religion when he writes, for it is God who is working in you, both to will and to work according to his good purpose.

10:26.442 --> 10:29.426
He's saying that the basis on which

10:29.506 --> 10:34.473
you work out your salvation is that God is already at work in you.

10:36.116 --> 10:44.929
God supplies the purpose, the power, and the perseverance for us to continue working out our salvation.

10:44.969 --> 10:46.471
Again, not working for it.

10:47.232 --> 10:55.825
Paul is not calling the Philippians to spiritually pull themselves up by their bootstraps and studies calling them to cooperative grace.

10:57.487 --> 10:59.410
The same God who began the good work

10:59.522 --> 11:04.348
is actively energizing your obedience right now.

11:04.368 --> 11:06.751
Right now.

11:06.771 --> 11:09.034
You're not trying to manufacture holiness.

11:09.995 --> 11:15.602
Rather, you are responding to a God who's already reshaping you from the inside out.

11:18.906 --> 11:22.090
And that's why our bottom line today is not gonna be try harder.

11:24.893 --> 11:26.896
This is not about self-effort.

11:26.916 --> 11:28.658
It's not about spiritual willpower.

11:29.154 --> 11:30.756
It's not about moral bootstrapping.

11:31.557 --> 11:35.543
It's work out what God is already working in you.

11:37.486 --> 11:40.791
Work out what God is already working in you.

11:43.054 --> 11:50.905
And so Paul then turns in verse 14 and gets painfully practical with the Philippian believers when he says, do everything without grumbly and arguing.

11:51.546 --> 11:52.367
This is easy, right?

11:52.427 --> 11:53.749
None of us complain ever, right?

11:56.493 --> 11:56.593
Yeah.

11:56.613 --> 11:57.234
Everything.

11:58.434 --> 11:59.055
Everything.

11:59.075 --> 12:00.817
A key word right there.

12:01.238 --> 12:01.638
Everything.

12:02.419 --> 12:04.041
Everything without grumbling or arguing.

12:04.562 --> 12:05.984
Not just the spiritual things.

12:06.725 --> 12:07.946
Not just the big things.

12:08.667 --> 12:10.109
Not just the things we enjoy.

12:10.149 --> 12:12.432
Not just the occasional things.

12:13.253 --> 12:14.395
He says everything.

12:16.858 --> 12:20.823
And grumbling, by the way, for Paul is more than mere belly aching.

12:22.625 --> 12:26.290
It's a posture of distrust toward God.

12:27.970 --> 12:34.318
It's redeemed people talking about life like God hasn't been faithful, like God isn't there.

12:36.921 --> 12:44.831
Now, of course, Paul is also making this statement with a reliance on the Old Testament story that Paul is very familiar with.

12:44.871 --> 12:46.373
Keep in mind, Paul is a Pharisee.

12:46.653 --> 12:48.736
He's a Jewish person rooted in the Scriptures.

12:49.477 --> 12:51.159
He knows his people's story.

12:52.440 --> 12:57.106
And of course, he's alluding to the story of Israel being delivered from Egypt

12:57.410 --> 13:03.116
and then grumbling their way into division and ultimately loss.

13:03.136 --> 13:12.907
The Israelites had experienced deliverance from the enslavement under Pharaoh of Egypt, but they didn't work out their deliverance.

13:14.188 --> 13:17.632
And Paul is saying to the church, don't repeat their story.

13:19.514 --> 13:22.617
Don't let salvation turn into complaint instead of trust.

13:24.520 --> 13:26.802
And Paul includes not only grumbling but arguing,

13:28.706 --> 13:36.757
He says, don't let the community that's meant to be one in the faith fracture over grumbling, pettiness, and disagreements.

13:38.700 --> 13:43.987
Because when this kind of grumbling and arguing dominates, unity collapses.

13:44.167 --> 13:48.734
And when unity collapses, our witness to the world around us dims.

13:51.818 --> 13:54.261
And that leads to what he says in verse 15.

13:55.623 --> 13:57.746
Paul continues with a so that,

13:58.882 --> 14:07.232
I always love these little phrases in the Bible that they should attune us to say, okay, he's going to base what he's about to say on what he just said.

14:07.272 --> 14:19.385
And what he just says is that this means that when we are obedient to God in response to the work he's already done and is doing in us without grumbling or arguing, it leads to something.

14:19.466 --> 14:21.488
It leads to a particular outcome.

14:22.970 --> 14:26.834
So he says that so that you may be blameless and innocent

14:27.362 --> 14:31.928
Children of God without fault in a crooked and perverted generation.

14:33.050 --> 14:34.111
Now why does that matter?

14:34.953 --> 14:37.536
Well again, Paul here is echoing Deuteronomy 32.

14:38.698 --> 14:46.529
Israel God's set apart people was called crooked in Deuteronomy 32, specifically in verses three through six.

14:47.710 --> 14:49.993
The world around the Philippians is crooked too.

14:51.015 --> 14:53.438
It's why Paul is in chains for his faith.

14:54.259 --> 14:56.242
Because the world around is in opposition

14:56.642 --> 14:57.263
to his faith.

14:58.003 --> 15:10.997
And Paul says that when we stand obedient to God in the middle of the surrounding crooked generation, we shine like stars, an image from Daniel 12, the wise shining in the darkness.

15:12.099 --> 15:14.781
Jesus himself said, you're the light of the world.

15:14.801 --> 15:18.465
So that is a church shine.

15:18.505 --> 15:20.488
How do we shine?

15:20.868 --> 15:23.851
How do you shine in the darkness?

15:25.333 --> 15:26.514
Not through branding.

15:27.138 --> 15:49.315
Not through volume, not through dominance and power, but through integrity, through unity, through non-grumbling obedience, by being a community that trusts instead of complains and the people who reflect Christ instead of fracture.

15:50.457 --> 15:53.202
That kind of community shines.

15:55.746 --> 15:57.849
And then in verse 16, he tells us how.

15:57.869 --> 16:01.995
It says, by holding fast to the word of life.

16:03.818 --> 16:10.307
This means clinging to the gospel, the words and the deeds and sacrifice of Jesus.

16:10.788 --> 16:18.900
When we anchor every part of our lives in the person of Jesus, it ultimately brings us true and abundant life.

16:19.862 --> 16:25.650
And Paul wants their faithfulness to be the proof that his labor wasn't wasted.

16:26.850 --> 16:31.574
In other words, a steady Philippian church even validates Paul's own ministry.

16:33.216 --> 16:41.744
Endurance in the faith, sticking to the word of life, remaining faithful to Jesus, is evidence.

16:44.166 --> 16:46.869
And Paul doesn't just command this posture, he models it.

16:48.290 --> 16:56.338
Because in verse 17, he writes, even if I am poured out as a drink offering on the sacrifice and service of your faith, I am glad and rejoice.

16:57.026 --> 16:59.310
Their faithful obedience is the main offering.

16:59.710 --> 17:03.797
And Paul says, if my suffering completes it, I'm willing.

17:05.420 --> 17:17.480
Now Paul, by saying that he's a drink offering being poured out, he's picturing himself as a libation, which is being poured out on top of their sacrifice.

17:17.560 --> 17:23.890
And in this world that the Philippians lived in, drink offerings were poured out as acts of worship to the gods.

17:25.762 --> 17:39.402
And so Paul is taking a religious and cultural idea that the Philippians would have been familiar with and would have been brought out of when they came to faith, and instead viewing himself as an offering being poured out to God.

17:41.185 --> 17:49.257
He is labored for their salvation and their endurance in the faith is worth his being poured out like a sacrifice.

17:50.499 --> 17:52.722
Paul is modeling biblical leadership.

17:53.538 --> 18:00.989
when he confidently declares that I will spend myself so that you can grow.

18:02.731 --> 18:04.855
It is worth being poured out for you.

18:06.938 --> 18:11.424
And finally, he includes in verse 18, he calls him to the same joy.

18:12.285 --> 18:15.991
He writes, in the same way, you should also be glad and rejoice with me.

18:17.393 --> 18:20.978
And again, like we've said throughout our study in Philippians,

18:21.442 --> 18:23.905
Joy here is not a denial of pain.

18:25.106 --> 18:34.457
Instead, it is a shared confidence that God is working, that the gospel is true, and that sacrifice is never, ever, ever wasted.

18:34.517 --> 18:38.121
And here's the thread running through it all.

18:39.382 --> 18:41.625
Obedience is not self-generated pressure.

18:42.145 --> 18:43.847
It is responsive participation.

18:44.288 --> 18:46.450
God works in and we work out.

18:46.562 --> 18:49.226
God shapes desire and we act on it.

18:49.566 --> 18:53.251
God energizes transformation and we cooperate with it.

18:53.852 --> 18:57.276
So the call of the passage is simple, but it's searching within us.

18:58.177 --> 19:01.482
Work out what God is working in you.

19:02.043 --> 19:05.387
Let the inner transformation become visible obedience.

19:05.848 --> 19:11.595
Let the humility of Christ take concrete form in the way you live and conduct yourself.

19:11.836 --> 19:16.562
Let the obedience of grumbling, or let the absence of grumbling reveal

19:16.802 --> 19:17.243
trust.

19:18.324 --> 19:20.747
Let your unity shine in a broken world.

19:21.448 --> 19:24.732
Let your life prove the gospel is real.

19:25.773 --> 19:29.137
Not by trying harder, but by letting God work deeper.

19:30.178 --> 19:32.741
Let your outer life reflect God's inner work.

19:34.323 --> 19:38.669
Work out what God is working in you.

19:40.491 --> 19:43.755
But what might that look like to work out what God is working in you?

19:43.835 --> 19:46.258
Well first,

19:46.562 --> 19:58.639
what Paul is saying implies that we are open to what God is working in us, that we are in regular prayer and that we are engaging regularly with scripture.

20:02.104 --> 20:11.698
I actually read a long survey one time that followed people in faith over a long number of years

20:12.418 --> 20:17.423
And it assessed how often they were doing spiritual practices like prayer and engagement with scripture.

20:18.064 --> 20:31.758
And they found that one of the most telling ways or one of the most revealing ways that would lead to transformation was if a person engaged with scripture four or more times a week.

20:33.539 --> 20:39.986
That didn't mean that they sat down and they read 10 chapters of the Bible every day for all of eternity.

20:41.474 --> 20:44.637
It might have meant that they engage with scripture and church like we're doing right now.

20:46.119 --> 20:47.960
Maybe you read a chapter on Monday.

20:48.741 --> 20:53.886
Maybe you got together in a small group or an ABF and you studied through a passage together.

20:54.427 --> 21:01.634
Those kinds of engagement of scripture ended up being the point that led to people's transformation.

21:02.895 --> 21:03.976
They became kinder.

21:04.017 --> 21:09.522
They became more patient, more joyful, more giving.

21:10.370 --> 21:13.175
because they were engaged with the word of God.

21:16.280 --> 21:25.395
And so it's important before we start getting into the working out portion that we take stock of whether we are open to God's working in in us.

21:27.298 --> 21:29.762
Daily, daily.

21:30.683 --> 21:37.234
But supposing we are remaining open to God's work in us, what might it look like in real life circumstances to work it out?

21:39.458 --> 21:45.425
I was thinking this week about some ordinary life circumstances, so let's consider a few scenarios.

21:47.648 --> 22:06.770
When you feel pressure at work, when you feel pressure to massage the numbers, to protect your position, working out what God is working in you means choosing quiet integrity over climbing the ladder and career advantage.

22:09.922 --> 22:12.084
Or how about the group chat that you're in with your friends?

22:13.025 --> 22:13.786
Those are fun, right?

22:16.549 --> 22:28.140
When it fills up with sarcasm and complaint, working out what God is working in you might mean refusing to bond through negativity and choosing steady faithfulness instead.

22:31.784 --> 22:38.290
When you're exhausted as a parent and your child pushes you one more time,

22:39.458 --> 22:40.079
One more time.

22:42.121 --> 22:48.468
Working out what God is working in you may mean slowing your tone instead of raising your voice.

22:51.772 --> 22:56.237
When you're rehearsing your defense in a marital spat, because we all got a win, right?

22:58.279 --> 23:03.405
Working out what God is working in you may mean apologizing first instead of winning the argument.

23:06.208 --> 23:07.570
When you feel overlooked,

23:08.258 --> 23:09.700
or like you're not measuring up.

23:10.801 --> 23:17.850
Working out what God is working in you may mean choosing contentment over constant comparison with others.

23:20.934 --> 23:27.342
At church, when decisions of style or practice don't align with your preferences.

23:29.525 --> 23:36.914
Working out what God is working in you means praying before criticizing and serving without resentment.

23:39.746 --> 23:52.922
When you feel a new conviction, a new hunger for scripture, or a new discomfort with old habits, working out what God is working in you may simply mean responding to that nudge instead of ignoring it.

23:55.826 --> 24:08.882
And when loving faithfully feels costly and unseen, working out what God is working in you may mean staying present and joyful, even when it feels

24:09.442 --> 24:14.769
Like you're being poured out, like a drink offering, like a sacrifice.

24:18.014 --> 24:19.476
Let me ask you something simple.

24:20.798 --> 24:23.301
Where is God already pressing on your heart?

24:26.005 --> 24:28.188
Where is he reshaping your desires?

24:29.770 --> 24:32.234
Where is he nudging you toward obedience?

24:34.197 --> 24:38.162
And before you answer that, let me tell you something I've been watching up close.

24:40.418 --> 24:46.267
I had a real-life picture that really encapsulates this point for me.

24:47.649 --> 24:50.933
My family Christmas got pushed back to January 31st.

24:51.194 --> 24:53.517
It was a late Christmas.

24:55.540 --> 25:00.488
The reason was because my dad was scheduled to have knee surgery in early December.

25:02.210 --> 25:10.322
And he ended up getting sick with a cold that turned into a viral infection.

25:11.138 --> 25:13.401
And he had a delay surgery by two weeks.

25:14.903 --> 25:20.070
And his surgery was going to happen mere days before our family Christmas gathering was going to be.

25:21.031 --> 25:23.614
And we're a bunch that doesn't like to leave each other out.

25:24.736 --> 25:27.960
I wouldn't have felt right not seeing my dad there, to be honest with you.

25:29.181 --> 25:31.545
So we pushed it back to January 31st.

25:31.605 --> 25:38.834
So my dad had a surgery in, you know, every, every surgery, you always wait and

25:39.234 --> 25:43.439
And you get the word, because I'm three hours away, and the surgery was a success.

25:44.240 --> 25:47.204
That's what they always say when your favorite athlete goes through surgery, right?

25:47.724 --> 25:48.546
It was a success.

25:50.348 --> 25:53.131
Because surgeons, they know they never mess up.

25:55.274 --> 25:56.075
It was a success.

25:58.658 --> 26:06.327
But the doctor doing exactly what needed to be done structurally noticed that he repaired the issue in his knee.

26:07.369 --> 26:08.370
But the recovery,

26:09.346 --> 26:10.828
Well, that was harder than expected.

26:13.610 --> 26:15.072
There were complications.

26:15.572 --> 26:18.535
My dad ended up having fevers every night for a month.

26:20.637 --> 26:23.861
I got to be honest with you, I had asked for updates from him or my mom.

26:25.222 --> 26:26.584
And I was getting a little freaked out.

26:28.726 --> 26:30.087
Didn't know what any of that means.

26:30.227 --> 26:33.791
And as you already know, I've told all of you a million times, I have anxiety.

26:34.552 --> 26:36.914
So my head started going to bad places.

26:40.002 --> 26:44.708
And things just made recovery feel nearly impossible.

26:44.788 --> 26:54.641
My dad had no energy to even do the stretches and the walking that were required for his knee to continue to heal.

26:54.701 --> 26:57.885
And of course, this all surprised my dad.

26:57.945 --> 27:03.693
My dad has recovered from much more grueling surgeries this far easier than before.

27:04.574 --> 27:07.538
My dad does not sit around ever, even when he should.

27:08.898 --> 27:12.182
So he's definitely a get to work on the rehab kind of person.

27:13.064 --> 27:13.524
And he couldn't.

27:15.547 --> 27:18.110
This won't be that bad of handled tougher, he thought.

27:19.152 --> 27:32.189
But after surgery comes physical therapy and therapy didn't feel like victory, it felt slow, it felt repetitive, it felt uncomfortable, and the surrounding issues made it at times feel impossible.

27:34.252 --> 27:35.634
Now the knee was technically fixed.

27:38.434 --> 27:44.460
But if you can't move it, if you can't stretch, if you can't do the exercises, the strength cannot return the way it should.

27:44.520 --> 27:50.365
The surgery was the decisive work, but the therapy is the daily participation.

27:50.426 --> 27:59.454
And sometimes the therapy hurts more than expected, especially when you have roadblocks from being able to give yourself to the therapy.

28:02.737 --> 28:04.439
And here's the key.

28:04.719 --> 28:07.602
The exercises don't create the healing.

28:09.730 --> 28:15.777
They cooperate with what the surgeon had already accomplished.

28:15.798 --> 28:22.205
And of course, in this case, in my dad's case, other factors got in the way from being able to cooperate.

28:23.347 --> 28:25.770
My dad's recovery from knee surgery was a lot like life.

28:28.353 --> 28:33.359
God has began doing a work in you at the moment of your salvation.

28:33.419 --> 28:35.542
And your intention is good.

28:36.363 --> 28:38.866
I'm gonna give myself constantly over to God.

28:41.922 --> 28:45.087
And yet life throws its curveballs all the time.

28:45.127 --> 28:48.152
You run into circumstances at work.

28:50.515 --> 28:58.067
You have loved ones that get ill. Life throws you all sorts of speed bumps on the way.

28:58.127 --> 29:05.478
And the question is, while I still give myself over to the work, even when the work gets hard.

29:07.681 --> 29:10.706
That's the message of Philippians 2, 12, or 18.

29:12.066 --> 29:13.869
God has done the saving work.

29:14.189 --> 29:15.451
It is decisive.

29:17.454 --> 29:19.017
You can't do it on your own.

29:19.057 --> 29:22.502
You cannot work your way to your salvation.

29:23.924 --> 29:28.271
But now we are called to work out what He has worked in.

29:28.311 --> 29:32.177
And sometimes that process surprises us.

29:33.319 --> 29:36.784
Sometimes it's harder than we thought it would be or should be.

29:37.505 --> 29:40.850
Sometimes growth is slower than we imagined it would be.

29:41.026 --> 29:48.137
Sometimes obedience feels more uncomfortable than we expected, but that discomfort isn't condemnation.

29:48.197 --> 29:56.189
It may be evidence, evidence that God is working in you.

29:59.234 --> 30:02.799
So let me ask you again, where is God already pressing in your heart?

30:05.142 --> 30:06.625
Maybe it's your tone at home.

30:08.287 --> 30:10.130
Maybe it's your integrity at work.

30:11.554 --> 30:13.496
Maybe it's your posture in church.

30:14.857 --> 30:19.382
Maybe it's a quiet conviction you've been ignoring, but you know you shouldn't.

30:21.924 --> 30:26.769
That pressure that you're feeling may not be shame.

30:28.210 --> 30:31.794
It may be the spirit strengthening what he has already repaired.

30:32.755 --> 30:35.197
And if that's true, you don't need to try any harder.

30:36.058 --> 30:37.740
You need to respond.

30:39.281 --> 30:39.922
Workout.

30:40.546 --> 30:41.968
what God is working in you.

30:42.608 --> 30:46.012
Not perfectly, not instantly, but faithfully.

30:48.155 --> 30:50.157
One small act of obedience at a time.

30:51.359 --> 30:52.720
One resisted grumble.

30:54.442 --> 30:55.804
One humble apology.

30:57.226 --> 31:00.790
One quiet decision to trust instead of complain.

31:00.850 --> 31:07.858
And when we do that together, we shine in the darkness.

31:09.634 --> 31:16.122
Not because we are strong, but because he is already at work.

31:17.163 --> 31:20.727
I hope on your way in that you got a communion packet this morning.

31:23.791 --> 31:33.202
We take communion each Sunday because we remember the work that God has already done through his son, Jesus.

31:33.922 --> 31:41.373
Jesus told His disciples on the night He was betrayed to take the bread and eat because it represents His body which is given for us.

31:42.294 --> 31:50.325
And He tells them likewise to drink from the cup because it represents His blood which was poured out for us.

31:52.448 --> 32:02.322
He acted obediently to the Father so that the work of the Father could take root in us, be done in us,

32:03.266 --> 32:05.991
and be worked out with us.

32:08.495 --> 32:15.948
And so I want you to take a moment and ponder the good work that God has already done, the grace given us through His Son Jesus.

32:16.909 --> 32:21.938
And after that moment of reflection, we will take communion together as one church family.

33:11.874 --> 33:17.319
I invite each one of you to take the bread and eat.

33:17.379 --> 33:19.501
This is his body which is given for us.

33:28.350 --> 33:31.292
And likewise, I invite you to take and drink from this cup.

33:32.113 --> 33:33.755
This is blood which is poured out for us.

33:40.461 --> 33:41.362
Please pray with me.

33:44.898 --> 34:14.290
Dear Lord God, I thank You for the reminder from Paul that the effort toward obedience is not ours to bear alone, but that You began to work for Your Son, Jesus, that He not only saves us by His act of faithfulness at the cross, but that He encourages us and inspires us

34:15.138 --> 34:30.326
toward a life of humility, of self-sacrifice, and of goodness and truth in this world that needs light and needs salt.

34:30.346 --> 34:33.693
I pray that you will help each and every one of us be reminded.

34:34.855 --> 34:38.642
For those of us that haven't made a decision of faith yet,

34:40.386 --> 34:43.370
to be your son, Jesus' disciples.

34:43.851 --> 34:59.091
I pray that you will begin to stir in their hearts the conviction that they can't go this life and the after alone that they need you and they can only get to you through Him.

35:00.473 --> 35:10.386
And I pray for those of us that have made that commitment, but maybe we're not always open to the work that you're doing in us, that you will help us to be open

35:11.010 --> 35:28.730
not turning into a checklist and bear the weight of our shoulders, but be open to the little opportunities to pray, to read scripture, to be open to your word and to your ways so that they can be transformed and live it out.

35:28.770 --> 35:39.922
And then Lord, I pray by the power of your spirit that our faith life doesn't stop at what we learn in your word, but that it is energized daily toward living it out.

35:40.770 --> 35:49.982
and not in the big grandiose ways that will make the news headlines or have books written, but will be those small moments.

35:51.564 --> 35:53.567
Maybe even nobody else sees, but you see.

35:55.049 --> 36:03.340
Help us to make those decisions each day by the power of your spirit and to act on those decisions by your will, your wonder, your might.

36:04.882 --> 36:06.785
Because we know that your ways are good.

36:07.526 --> 36:10.610
Even if we don't experience the benefit in the moment,

36:11.714 --> 36:13.900
We know that your ways are right and true.

36:15.444 --> 36:26.115
Help us in every facet of our lives, every step of faith that we take, and help us to always remember that you are with us in those, and it's in your son Jesus' name that we pray.

36:27.037 --> 36:27.378
Amen.

